12:57.270 --> 12:59.830
- Hannibal's good enough
for you.

13:04.880 --> 13:07.769
You should be afraid.

13:13.960 --> 13:16.554
I want you to have something.

13:31.240 --> 13:34.232
Whoever you are afraid of...

13:36.480 --> 13:39.404
...don't be afraid to use it.

13:39.450 --> 13:42.578
It takes 9mm rounds.

13:42.620 --> 13:45.043
Buy a box...

13:45.090 --> 13:48.912
find a range...

13:52.090 --> 13:54.320
Practice.

14:11.650 --> 14:13.618
- Please.

14:15.320 --> 14:17.982
- I would like
to tell you about camp.

14:18.020 --> 14:20.284
It was a wonderful
childhood experience

14:20.320 --> 14:22.288
that keeps
coming back to me.

14:22.320 --> 14:24.880
Papa paid for the whole thing,
every summer,

14:24.930 --> 14:29.253
all 125 campers
on Lake Michigan.

14:29.300 --> 14:31.598
- Your father
was a generous man.

14:31.630 --> 14:34.565
- I've continued
his charitable work today.

14:34.600 --> 14:37.160
Most of the campers
are unfortunates

14:37.210 --> 14:40.031
who will do anything
for a candy bar.

14:40.080 --> 14:42.332
Ha!Ha!Ha!

14:44.310 --> 14:47.518
Maybe I took advantage.
Maybe I was rough with them.

14:47.550 --> 14:50.189
I'm not holding
anything back.

14:50.220 --> 14:52.188
It's all OK.

14:52.220 --> 14:55.109
I got a walk on the charges.

14:55.160 --> 14:58.049
- What was your penance?
- I got 500 hours

14:58.090 --> 15:00.593
of community service.
I worked at the dog pound

15:00.630 --> 15:04.464
and I received
some court-ordered therapy.

15:04.500 --> 15:07.139
- Was therapy helpful?

15:07.170 --> 15:10.662
- I got the doctor involved
in something unethical,

15:10.710 --> 15:14.168
so he'd cut me some slack.

15:14.210 --> 15:17.008
- That's not helpful.

15:17.050 --> 15:20.315
- Papa called it
"altruistic punishment".

15:20.350 --> 15:22.545
- Mason...

15:22.580 --> 15:24.548
please...

15:24.590 --> 15:26.979
- Oh.

15:41.240 --> 15:43.299
Papa was a prodigy

15:43.340 --> 15:46.366
in the field of meat,
but his real

15:46.410 --> 15:49.937
genius was for human nature.

15:51.750 --> 15:54.310
He could look at a man...

15:54.350 --> 15:56.409
and see his weakness.

15:56.450 --> 15:58.486
- Your father is dead.

16:00.390 --> 16:03.427
A boy's illusions are no basis
for a man's life, Mason.

16:07.160 --> 16:09.697
Margot is the only family
you have left.

16:18.040 --> 16:20.008
- My sister loves me,
Dr. Lecter.

16:20.040 --> 16:22.508
She has to or she's destitute.

16:27.450 --> 16:30.988
- Vergers are
noted expansionists.

16:32.820 --> 16:35.983
- And I am the sole Verger heir.

16:40.100 --> 16:43.592
