17:32.650 --> 17:35.619
It's common for a killer

17:35.650 --> 17:37.743
to revisit their victims
after death,

17:37.790 --> 17:39.746
attend funerals,

17:39.790 --> 17:41.781
return to crime scenes.

17:43.630 --> 17:45.621
- Anyone suspicious?
- Besides me?

17:45.660 --> 17:47.799
- That was implied.

17:49.860 --> 17:52.226
- You were expecting me.

17:52.270 --> 17:54.636
- "It's common for a killer

17:54.670 --> 17:57.537
to revisit their victims
after death."

17:57.570 --> 18:00.471
- I'm not here to dance
on Freddie Lounds's grave

18:00.510 --> 18:03.104
if that's what
you're getting at.

18:03.150 --> 18:05.539
- You're not here looking
for her killer, either.

18:05.580 --> 18:09.744
You don't seem particularly
interested in the crowd.

18:09.780 --> 18:14.410
- Are you profiling me,
Dr. Bloom?

18:22.330 --> 18:25.390
I'm here because...

18:27.400 --> 18:29.732
....my psychiatrist suggested

18:29.770 --> 18:31.806
it would be therapeutic.

18:46.690 --> 18:48.715
I've been so preoccupied with

18:48.760 --> 18:51.820
taking a life, I'm, uh...

18:51.860 --> 18:54.727
having trouble wrapping my head
around making one.

18:57.270 --> 19:00.569
- When men become fathers,
they undergo biochemical changes

19:00.600 --> 19:04.309
that affect the way they think.

19:04.340 --> 19:07.173
- You said the same thing
happens when men become killers.

19:07.210 --> 19:09.508
- Fathers can be killers.

19:12.650 --> 19:15.244
What sort of father
would you be?

19:17.350 --> 19:20.353
- I would be a good father.

19:20.390 --> 19:23.188
- How quickly
we form attachments

19:23.230 --> 19:24.925
to something
that does not yet exist.

19:24.960 --> 19:27.656
- I'm not attached. I'm...

19:27.700 --> 19:29.725
I'm only...

19:29.760 --> 19:32.228
anticipating attachment.

19:34.370 --> 19:36.338
- We have
a deep-seated need

19:36.370 --> 19:38.338
to interact
with our children.

19:38.370 --> 19:40.804
It helps us discover
who we are.

19:42.810 --> 19:44.846
- Have you ever been a father?

19:44.880 --> 19:47.713
- I was to my sister.

19:50.720 --> 19:53.416
She was not my child,
but she was my charge.

19:56.560 --> 19:58.881
She taught me so much
about myself.

20:00.900 --> 20:04.267
Her name was... Mischa.

20:05.870 --> 20:07.599
- Was?

20:07.640 --> 20:09.995
- She's dead.

20:10.040 --> 20:12.668
Abigail reminded me
so much of her.

20:19.350 --> 20:21.409
- Why did you kill her?

20:24.290 --> 20:27.418
- What happened to Abigail
had to happen.

20:27.460 --> 20:30.020
There was no other way.

20:30.060 --> 20:33.291
- There was.

20:36.430 --> 20:38.819
But there isn't now.

20:40.840 --> 20:42.796
- Would you protect this child
in the way

20:42.840 --> 20:44.831
you couldn't protect Abigail?

20:49.010 --> 20:51.570
- I still dream about Abigail.

20:54.620 --> 20:57.817
I dream that I'm...

20:57.850 --> 21:00.717
teaching her how to fish.

21:03.330 --> 21:05.423
- I'm sorry...

21:05.460 --> 21:07.599
