25:44.170 --> 25:47.571
(horse whinnying)

25:47.610 --> 25:51.341
I need to share this wealth

25:51.380 --> 25:53.769
with a little Verger.

25:53.820 --> 25:57.586
- "A little Verger."
- Don't you want an heir,

25:57.620 --> 26:00.111
Margot?

26:00.150 --> 26:02.653
I want a baby Verger,

26:02.690 --> 26:04.658
my own baby.

26:04.690 --> 26:07.124
I have viable sperm.

26:07.160 --> 26:10.129
I think I'd have a son.
It'd be your heir too.

26:10.160 --> 26:12.822
Auntie Margot...

26:17.970 --> 26:20.359
I think a child

26:20.410 --> 26:24.244
may be what we need
to bring us closer together.

26:27.180 --> 26:29.216
- Maybe it is.

26:32.020 --> 26:33.954
- I've said it before,

26:33.990 --> 26:36.049
you've got a bloom.

26:38.190 --> 26:39.919
Rosy.

26:42.660 --> 26:46.619
Positively radiant.

26:46.670 --> 26:49.332
What is your secret?

26:55.740 --> 26:57.708
- Every creative act

26:57.750 --> 27:00.742
has its destructive
consequence, Will.

27:00.780 --> 27:03.078
The Hindu god Shiva

27:03.120 --> 27:06.089
is simultaneous
destroyer and creator.

27:08.090 --> 27:10.411
Who you were yesterday
is laid waste

27:10.460 --> 27:12.951
to give rise
to who you are today.

27:14.900 --> 27:18.996
- How many lies have had
to be... sanctified?

27:21.000 --> 27:25.061
How many consciences...
devastated?

27:25.110 --> 27:28.102
- As many as were necessary.

27:32.210 --> 27:34.747
- You sacrificed Abigail.

27:36.720 --> 27:38.688
You cared about her

27:38.720 --> 27:41.814
as much as I did.

27:41.860 --> 27:43.919
- Maybe more.

27:45.930 --> 27:48.956
But then, how much

27:49.000 --> 27:52.128
has God sacrificed?

27:54.770 --> 27:57.398
- What god do you pray to?

27:57.440 --> 27:59.829
- I don't pray.

27:59.870 --> 28:02.976
I have not been bothered
by any considerations of deity,

28:03.010 --> 28:06.377
other than to recognize
how my own modest actions

28:06.410 --> 28:09.971
pale beside those of God.

28:10.020 --> 28:13.012
- I prayed...

28:15.020 --> 28:17.352
...I would see Abigail again.

28:19.760 --> 28:21.853
- Well, your prayer
did not go entirely unanswered.

28:21.900 --> 28:23.891
You saw part of her.

28:25.900 --> 28:27.936
Will...

28:27.970 --> 28:31.235
should the universe contract,

28:31.270 --> 28:33.830
should time reverse

28:33.880 --> 28:37.748
and teacups come together...

28:37.780 --> 28:41.739
a place could be made
for Abigail in your world.

28:43.520 --> 28:45.886
- What place would that be?

28:47.890 --> 28:51.280
- You've lost a child, Will.

28:51.330 --> 28:53.992
It seems you're likely
to gain one.

28:57.160 --> 29:00.027
God is beyond measure

29:00.070 --> 29:03.039
in wanton malice...

29:03.070 --> 29:06.130
and matchless in his irony.

29:29.060 --> 29:31.164
- No, no, no.
Cancel that one.

29:37.270 --> 29:41.309
I remember

29:41.340 --> 29:44.173
walking the swine fairs

29:44.210 --> 29:46.246
with my father,

29:46.280 --> 29:48.840
looking over the competition.

29:48.880 --> 29:50.882
Papa's little silver knife

29:50.920 --> 29:54.811
ever ready
to slip out of his waistcoat

29:54.860 --> 29:57.556
and stick into the back of a pig

29:57.590 --> 30:00.024
to check the depth of fat.

30:00.060 --> 30:03.427
- Your education was an odd one.

30:03.460 --> 30:06.167
- Ha! Ha! Ha!

30:08.170 --> 30:10.365
Oh, those were good,
funny times.

30:10.400 --> 30:12.937
Papa would stab

30:12.970 --> 30:15.006
4-H show pigs

30:15.040 --> 30:17.008
who thought
everyone was their friend,

30:17.040 --> 30:20.100
scrubbed in milk
and baby powder.

30:20.150 --> 30:22.311
Such coddled little things.

30:26.250 --> 30:30.152
- Part of a show pig's
consideration is its happiness.

30:30.190 --> 30:33.057
- If we were truly considerate

30:33.090 --> 30:35.854
of a pig's happiness...

30:35.900 --> 30:38.061
we wouldn't eat them.

30:38.100 --> 30:41.297
- What about Margot's happiness?

30:41.340 --> 30:43.399
- Papa taught me
how to stick the knife in

30:43.440 --> 30:45.408
only as deep as necessary,

30:45.440 --> 30:48.603
to test the thickness
of her skin.

30:50.610 --> 30:53.647
- You miscalculated...

30:53.680 --> 30:55.944
struck a nerve.

30:55.980 --> 30:59.313
- Margot would love
to stick a knife into me,

30:59.350 --> 31:02.353
and it wouldn't be to test
the thickness of my skin.

31:02.390 --> 31:05.188
- She tried
to kill you once already.

31:05.230 --> 31:07.585
- "To a male heir

31:07.630 --> 31:10.098
confirmed as my descendent..."

31:10.130 --> 31:12.360
It's a very clever loophole

31:12.400 --> 31:14.368
she's found in Papa's will.

31:14.400 --> 31:16.960
Clearly, he did not
take into account

31:17.000 --> 31:20.504
how resourceful she is.

31:22.380 --> 31:24.348
- Neither did you.

31:24.380 --> 31:26.405
- I can be resourceful too.

31:26.450 --> 31:29.419
If she's not pregnant,
she will be.

31:29.450 --> 31:32.886
Margot's very tenacious
that way.

31:34.990 --> 31:38.482
- This child would be a Verger.

31:38.530 --> 31:41.693
You would have an heir
to carry on the family name,

31:41.730 --> 31:44.597
to carry on your name.

31:44.630 --> 31:47.121
- I'd have an heir...

31:47.170 --> 31:49.934
only ifI die.

31:49.970 --> 31:52.006
(He scoffs.)

31:54.380 --> 31:56.632
One observes only things

31:56.680 --> 31:58.671
which are already
on the mind.

32:02.020 --> 32:04.079
What's on your mind?

32:05.750 --> 32:08.082
- I'm feeling pressure to
believe something I don't trust,

32:08.120 --> 32:10.213
and that pressure

32:10.260 --> 32:13.149
is making me paranoid.

32:13.190 --> 32:16.921
- Who's pressuring you?

32:18.700 --> 32:22.090
- Will.

32:26.710 --> 32:29.679
- We'll never really
be alone, will we?

32:29.710 --> 32:33.146
He'll always be in the room.

32:35.150 --> 32:38.381
- Do you feel like you're
helping him? Making progress?

32:38.420 --> 32:41.218
- Will is finally
finding himself.

32:41.260 --> 32:43.285
He's getting better.

32:43.320 --> 32:45.720
- Doesn't seem
to be getting better.

32:48.500 --> 32:51.060
- Are you questioning
my therapy?

32:53.130 --> 32:55.132
- I'm questioning everything.

32:57.140 --> 32:59.700
It's all blurry and subjective.

33:02.740 --> 33:05.277
I feel empty,

33:05.310 --> 33:07.471
like I've given blood.

33:12.390 --> 33:15.211
- Alana, you've given
more than blood.

33:55.400 --> 33:58.597
Have you been firing a gun?

34:00.700 --> 34:03.669
- I told you
I was feeling paranoid.

35:26.920 --> 35:29.252
(machine beeping)

35:35.230 --> 35:37.596
- Poor Margot...

35:37.630 --> 35:40.360
you just can't win.

35:49.910 --> 35:52.606
I have to...

35:52.650 --> 35:55.175
remove this temptation.

35:55.220 --> 35:57.711
(Margot breathing hard)

36:08.700 --> 36:11.624
They're going
to find something wrong

36:11.670 --> 36:14.332
with your lady parts, Margot.

36:14.370 --> 36:16.736
Or so the record will state.

36:18.710 --> 36:20.928
The doctor will advise me

36:20.970 --> 36:23.530
that it's best

36:23.580 --> 36:26.276
if they take...

36:26.310 --> 36:28.278
everything.

36:28.320 --> 36:31.346
I'm afraid the only person

36:31.390 --> 36:33.745
you'll be celebrating
Mother's Day with

36:33.790 --> 36:37.385
is me.

37:09.390 --> 37:11.779
- The most terrifying thing
in the world

37:11.830 --> 37:13.650
can be a lucid moment.

37:17.900 --> 37:19.959
What are you up to?

37:23.300 --> 37:25.632
- I'm not sure I know what
you're talking about, Dr. Bloom.

37:32.750 --> 37:36.015
- I think you know.

37:36.050 --> 37:38.280
You're not fooling me, Jack.

37:38.320 --> 37:41.881
- I'm not trying to fool you.
- You're lying.

37:41.920 --> 37:45.356
You're all lying.

37:45.390 --> 37:48.291
Will. Hannibal.

37:48.330 --> 37:51.367
You're lying to each other,
and they're lying to you.

37:51.400 --> 37:53.891
- Tell me what you believe
is happening.

37:53.930 --> 37:55.898
- What do I believe?

37:55.940 --> 37:58.033
What do you believe?

38:02.040 --> 38:04.474
Do you believe
Will killed Freddie Lounds?

38:04.510 --> 38:06.740
- No, I don't.

38:06.780 --> 38:09.578
- Do you think Dr. Chilton's
the Chesapeake Ripper?

38:09.620 --> 38:12.282
- There was overwhelming--
- STOP LYING, JACK!

38:17.390 --> 38:19.529
(Sigh)

38:19.560 --> 38:23.451
You think you've moved
your pieces around so cleverly.

38:25.830 --> 38:28.560
- What's changed, Alana?

38:28.600 --> 38:30.761
- I have no confidence

38:30.800 --> 38:33.439
that I know
Hannibal Lecter anymore.

38:35.780 --> 38:39.477
Even with as much as you know
or think you know Hannibal,
you don't know him either.

38:41.550 --> 38:43.871
And you don't know Will.

38:43.920 --> 38:47.708
You are going to lose, Jack!

38:51.160 --> 38:53.583
If you haven't lost already.

39:03.040 --> 39:05.361
- I want you to come with me.

39:24.430 --> 39:26.625
- How was my funeral?

39:32.170 --> 39:34.491
(machine beeping)

40:09.800 --> 40:12.530
(strange tribal song)

40:16.710 --> 40:18.803
(Middle Eastern music)

40:36.530 --> 40:38.919
(The music stops abruptly.)
- Carlo?

40:38.970 --> 40:43.088
Carlo, I don't think
they've had enough to...

40:51.240 --> 40:53.447
You must be the baby daddy.

40:56.250 --> 40:59.048
Excuse me if I_don't
offer you a Cigar.

41:11.000 --> 41:14.993
I'm gonna feed you
to my pigs. Carlo!

41:15.040 --> 41:17.736
(Mason laughing crazily)

41:17.770 --> 41:20.466
(both grunting)

41:22.680 --> 41:25.649
- Do you think it was
Margot's idea to have an heir?

41:27.650 --> 41:31.689
You think it was your idea
to take it from her?

41:31.720 --> 41:34.086
My idea

41:34.120 --> 41:37.715
to come here and kill you?

41:37.760 --> 41:41.252
The only thing
that you, your sister,

41:41.290 --> 41:44.020
and I have in common

41:44.060 --> 41:48.121
is the same psychiatrist.

41:56.840 --> 41:59.877
(Mason laughs.)

42:01.950 --> 42:04.885
If Dr. Lecter
had his druthers...

42:04.920 --> 42:09.516
you'd be wrapped
around a bullet right now.

42:14.030 --> 42:15.657
(Will uncocks the gun.)

42:17.860 --> 42:21.023
Dr. Lecter is the one you want
to be feeding to your pigs.

42:31.080 --> 42:33.742
***

